{"_path":"/security/project-sekai-2022/vocaloid-heardle","_dir":"project-sekai-2022","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"","title":"Vocaloid Heardle","description":"Category: Misc\nPoints: 325\nSolved By: Apicius","body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"h1","props":{"id":"vocaloid-heardle"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Vocaloid Heardle"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Category:"}]},{"type":"text","value":" Misc\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Points:"}]},{"type":"text","value":" 325\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Solved By:"}]},{"type":"text","value":" Apicius"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"challenge"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Challenge"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"blockquote","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Well, it’s just too usual to hide a flag in stegano, database, cipher, or server. What if we decide to sing it out instead?"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"em","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Author: pamLELcu"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Files: "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"flag.mp3"}]},{"type":"text","value":", "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"vocaloid_heardle.py"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"solution"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Solution"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Before looking at the python script, I thought I'd first give "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"flag.mp3"}]},{"type":"text","value":" a listen. Upon listening to it, it seems that it's spliced together vocaloid songs of about 3 seconds in length each, with the whole file being 33 seconds long."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Next up was to check out the script. I went through the script and added comments detailing what it was doing in order to properly understand it."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"","src":"/assets/images/commented-code.png"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The function of this script is to take a file "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"flag.txt"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and encode it into unicode characters, fetch a song with an ID that matches the unicode character, and then add the first three seconds of it to the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"flag.mp3"}]},{"type":"text","value":" file."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Rather than coming up with a fancy way to do this, I solved it using a rather simple method. I created a file named "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"flag.txt"}]},{"type":"text","value":", supplied unicode characters 33 through 126, and then ran the program. This gave me a folder full of tracks with the title being a number that corresponds with a unicode character. From here I split "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"flag.mp3"}]},{"type":"text","value":" into 11 parts, and then listened to each song and matched it with a unicode character. The resulting characters being:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"[118, 48, 67, 97, 108, 111, 73, 100, 60, 51, 117]"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When I took these numbers and converted them to ASCII I was given the flag:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Flag:"}]},{"type":"text","value":" "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SEKAI{v0CaloId<3u}"}]}]}],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[{"id":"challenge","depth":2,"text":"Challenge"},{"id":"solution","depth":2,"text":"Solution"}]}},"_type":"markdown","_id":"content:security:project-sekai-2022:vocaloid-heardle.md","_source":"content","_file":"security/project-sekai-2022/vocaloid-heardle.md","_extension":"md"}